<TITLE> Seas turn rough, no depression likely </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 2 (bdnews24.com)The Bay of Bengal has once again been behaving erratically, whipping up huge waves amid gusty to squally winds after hardly a week after cyclone 'Aila' ravaged the south-western coasts. "The seas seemed a bit choppy because the thunder-carrying monsoon clouds have been active over the Bay," assistant meteorologist Md Rasheduzzaman told bdnews24.com on Tuesday. "But there is no possibility of another depression or cyclone to brew." The ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazaar and Mongla have been advised to keep local cautionary signal three hoisted until further notice, he said. 
